 on intelligence in children: a meta-analysis of studies conducted in China |journal=Asia Pacific Journal of Clinical Nutrition |volume=14 |issue=1 |pages=32\u201342 |pmid=15734706 |ref={{harvid|Qian et al.|2005}}}}\n<!--Reichman 2005-->\n*{{Cite journal |last=Reichman |first=Nancy E. |date=2005 |title=Low birth weight and school readiness |journal=The Future of Children |volume=15 |issue=1 |pages=91\u2013116 |doi=10.1353/foc.2005.0008 |issn=1054-8289 |pmid=16130543 |ref={{harvid|Reichman|2005}}}}\n<!--Reuning 1988-->\n*{{Cite encyclopedia |year=1988 |encyclopedia=Human Abilities in Cultural Context |publisher=Cambridge University Press |last=Reuning |first=Helmut |editor-last=Irvine |editor-first=SH |pages=453\u2013486 |doi=10.1017/CBO9780511574603.018 |isbn=978-0-511-57460-3 |ref=harv |chapter-url=http://ebooks.cambridge.org/chapter.jsf?bid=CBO9780511574603&cid=CBO9780511574603A028 |editor2-last=Berry |editor2-first=JW |chapter=Testing Bushmen in the Central Kalahari}}\n<!--Richardson 2004-->\n*{{Cite journal |last=Richardson |first=K |year=2004 |title=Book Review: IQ and the Wealth of Nations |journal=Heredity |volume=92 |issue=4 |pages=359\u201360 |doi=10.1038/sj.hdy.6800418 |ref=harv}}\n<!--Rindermann & Thompson 2013-->\n*{{Cite journal |last=Rindermann |first=Heiner |last2=Thompson |first2=James |date=November 2013 |title=Ability rise in NAEP and narrowing ethnic gaps? |journal=Intelligence |volume=41 |issue=6 |pages=821\u2013831 |doi=10.1016/j.intell.2013.06.016 |ref=harv}}\n<!--Rose 2009-->\n*{{Cite journal |last=Rose |first=Steven |year=2009 |title=Darwin 200: Should scientists study race and IQ? NO: Science and society do not benefit |journal=Nature |volume=457 |issue=7231 |pages=786\u20138 |bibcode=2009Natur.457..786R |doi=10.1038/457786a |pmid=19212384 |ref=harv}}\n<!--Roth et al. 2001 -->\n*{{Cite journal |last=Roth |first=PL |last2=Bevier |first2=CA |last3=Bobko |first3=P |last4=Switzer |first4=FS, III |last5=Tyler |first5=P |year=2001 |title=Ethnic gr